    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "This 996-generation Carrera 2 offers a visceral, analog driving experience powered by a 3.4L flat-six engine with VarioCam variable valve timing. The longitudinal rear-engine layout provides exceptional traction and weight transfer characteristics, managed by a precise G96 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanical integrity is a priority: the IMS bearing has been retrofitted with an LN Engineering dual-row solution, and the Rear Main Seal (RMS) has been replaced. The suspension maintains its factory-spec geometry with refreshed bushings, ensuring the multi-link rear setup delivers the communicative feedback these chassis are known for. Minor cosmetic imperfections exist, but the powertrain and cooling system\u2014including a new high-flow water pump\u2014are dialed in for spirited performance. A purist-spec RWD example ready for the twisties.",
